# ─── Duffel — live flight search ─────────────────────────────────────
# Dashboard → (your org) → Developers → Access tokens → New token.
# Use a TEST token (starts with `duffel_test_`) for development — it hits the
# same API but never creates real, billable bookings. Swap to a live token only
# in production. Server-side only — never shipped to the app.
DUFFEL_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ─── Google Places API (New) — restaurant discovery ──────────────────
# From Google Cloud Console → APIs & services → Credentials. Restrict the key
# to "Places API (New)". Server-side only — never shipped to the app.
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=

# ─── LiteAPI (Nuitée) — hotel search ─────────────────────────────────
# From dashboard.liteapi.travel → Developers → API Keys. Sandbox key starts
# with sand_ (test), production with prod_. Server-side only.
LITEAPI_KEY=

# ─── Vercel AI Gateway ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In PRODUCTION on Vercel you do NOT need this — the gateway is authed
# automatically via the injected VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN (OIDC). Leave it unset there.
#
# For LOCAL development only, create an AI Gateway key in the Vercel dashboard
# (AI Gateway → API Keys) and put it here so `npm run dev` can reach the gateway.
AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional shared secret (Bilt → Vercel hop) ──────────────────────
# If set, /api/estimate requires an x-estimate-secret header matching this value.
# Leave UNSET for the MVP (the MD says skip for the demo, add if time).
# If you set it here, also set the SAME value in the Bilt app's fetch headers.
ESTIMATE_SHARED_SECRET=
